Potential Red Flags

Someone asks for your DTE account number  
DTE Energy DOES NOT ask customers to provide their account numbers. Customers will be asked to validate account information such as the billing zip code, or last four digits of their Social Security number prior to discussing account details to protect our customers’ private information. DTE Energy DOES NOT call for payment if the account is in good standing. If a customer is behind on payments, DTE will mail a warning notice, providing the steps to restore the account to good standing and continue service.   

Bullying   

Alarm bells should ring when someone calls and says a crew is on the way to shut off service unless there’s an immediate payment. The more aggressive the caller, the more skeptical customers should be.   

Demanding a specific form of payment  

DTE provides a variety of traditional payment options, but we never demand a specific type. Scammers will often request payments through unusual forms, such as cryptocurrency like Bitcoin, money transferring apps like Zelle or Cash App, pre-paid debit cards like Green Dot or Western Union wire transfers.  

On the Phone   

DO NOT trust your caller ID. Scammers are using caller ID spoofing to make the call appear to originate from DTE Energy. If you suspect the call may be fraudulent, hang up and call DTE customer service at 800.477.4747. Similar scams also spoof caller ID and claim to be the IRS and other credible sources.   

Ask for identification. Pull out your most recent DTE Energy bill and ask the caller to tell you your account number and the amount due. 

If you have received a call of this nature and believe you are the victim of fraud, contact your local police immediately. Please also alert DTE afterwards by calling 800.477.4747.  

Scammers also utilize text messages to request payment. Do not click on any links, scan any barcodes or make any payments via an unusual text message.

The Spartan Sword Pledge Ceremony at John D. Dingell VA Medical Center was emotional. 

It was created to inspire veterans and first responders
to take the "Spartan Pledge" - a promise written
by Iraq War Veteran, Boone Cutler. The pledge is made between veterans to not attempt suicide without reaching out to their battle buddy first. 

We are losing over 20 veterans a day to suicide. The cost of war is real and we are failing our veterans by not doing more to address the impacts of sending them to war.

The Straight Farmhouse Historic District in Garden City will now house a “Rosie the Riveter” Rose Garden. It was a beautiful tribute to the women who stepped up and served our country during the second World War, who became known as “Rosie the Riveters.

Rep. Plaskett courageously served as one of the impeachment managers last year. I was an awe of her determination and brilliance. Welcome to Michigan! 

12th Congressional District is so proud be part of Oakland County where communities have come together over and over again to organize, mobilize and fight against fascism. We are going to get stronger every year with everyone at the table.

In the 12th Congressional District, we all know someone who is a UAW worker or retiree. Many of us come from UAW homes. We are the @uaw.union. 

When the same Big 3 struggled to stay afloat in 2008/09, it was the UAW workers who took the biggest hit. Plant closures destroyed communities. Removal of COLA hurt working families. Now, with the billions of dollars in record profits, they are leaving workers struggling. Not anymore. 

We are going to fight and win!

Join my team and I this coming Sunday, September 17th at 3 pm to learn how you can support our striking UAW members. 

National Lawyers Guild Michigan Chapter will be discussing how you can become a legal observer. We will also be sharing the list of donation requests from UAW Local 900 (MAPP strikers in Wayne). 

Register at mobilize.us/s/QbDmtP

I grieve the Palestinian and Israeli lives lost yesterday, today, and every day. I am determined as ever to fight for a just future where everyone can live in peace, without fear and with true freedom, equal rights, and human dignity. 

The path to that future must include lifting the blockade, ending the occupation, and dismantling the apartheid system that creates the suffocating, dehumanizing conditions that can lead to resistance. 

The failure to recognize the violent reality of living under siege, occupation, and apartheid makes no one safer. No person, no child anywhere should have to suffer or live in fear of violence. We cannot ignore the humanity in each other. 

As long as our country provides billions in unconditional funding to support the apartheid government, this heartbreaking cycle of violence will continue.

I can't take this anymore. The hate and racist rhetoric coming out of Washington is pushing incendiary, hateful, and dehumanizing anti-Palestinian & anti-Muslim rhetoric that must be called out. 

Stop it! All of you. 

Wadea did not deserve his 6 year old body to be mutilated 26 times with a knife. He didn't deserve his country to have people believe he is sub human. 

Allah Yerhamo.

The answer to war crimes is not more war crimes. Please support Congresswoman @coribush @andrechronicles @summerleeforpa @deliaramirezil @jamaalbowmanny @repbonnie @repchuygarcia @repjackson @aoc @ilhanmn @ayannapressley @rep_velazquez as they stand on the right side of history in demanding our country facilitate a ceasefire to help save lives.

Transformative change does not come from the Oval Office or Congress, it comes from organizing in the streets, in our communities, and demanding that change. Thank you to all of these loving and beautiful organizations for supporting the end of violence.

🚨🚨☎️ Tomorrow night, Sunday, October 29th at 8 p.m. (EST), join me and fellow elected officials across the country for a NATIONAL CALL 📞 for a #ceasefire.

Mr. President, the American people are not with you on this one. You need to support a #ceasefire now. We will remember where you stood come next year.

Zakaria Alarayshi, a Michigan resident, trapped in Gaza, sent me the following text and voice note this morning:

"This is a message is for President Biden. This war must stop. Women and children are dying every minute. Entire families are being wiped out in their homes. We have no food, no water and no medicine and nowhere to go. We are dying slowly. We ask you and we ask our president for an immediate ceasefire and for help to get us out of here. No where is safe in Gaza. They asked us to go south, we did. And now they are bombing our streets, our homes and our shops. We need immediate help. Is there any humanity left in the world?"

The voices of those who on the ground in Gaza need to be heard now more than ever.

This is a displaced mother in Gaza. She is carrying her baby through the destruction of war with no place safe to go. This is all I need to see to understand the cruelty of the ongoing war crimes being committed by the Israeli government funded by our country using American weapons. 

International laws were created to protect and save the lives of civilians like this mother and her child. Instead, they are being brushed aside and ignored by the world community as they tacitly comply with ethnic cleansing and genocide. 

This must end now. She and her baby deserve to live free from violence and racist and oppressive policies.
 
Ceasefire now.

It is unacceptable that Meta is not giving my Instagram account access to the account status tab which is where you are to be notified of any violations or false information that you are posting.

This means I have not had access on hold to any post that could be the reason reason my account is being flagged as” repeatedly, posting false information”

This also means I don’t have any access to the appeals process for individual post or from the threat that came yesterday that my account would be platformed permanently. 

I’m receiving dozens of messages that when ppl try to engage with my account they get these prompts claiming allegedly that I have repeatedly posted false information.

while I have in the last 40+ days of this ethnic cleansing campaign posted a video that was not verified to be in Gaza. I have taken them down very quickly and corrected them unlike Most and News organization social media platforms who continue to pedal propaganda that has been debunked and discredited.

I can only assume that I am being targeted along with other prominent accounts, who advocate for the basic human rights of Palestinian people, and are willing to use the appropriate terminology to describe what Israel is doing in Gaza, which is ethnic, cleansing and apartheid and collective punishment!  I should note that countless other accounts from News organizations and individuals with much larger followings that spew vitriol and anti-Semitic and anti-Islamic and anti-Palestinian dehumanizing racist, insightful content, are not being threatened with the same pattern and frequency.

well, this may not be surprising to me, or too many of us who have seen how Instagram and Meta have been guilty of silencing and censoring Palestinian invoices we should still speak out and demand equality on these platforms.

I ask that Instagram prove to me what my false information posts are. And if it was repeated what are they? I didn’t post false information repeatedly. This is targeted. Without proof to penalize my account while depriving me of my account status tab in Instagram. Is this a “glitch” or am I being targeted?

Yesterday, a young man who I have known most of his life informed me that on his @americanair flight AA2829 home from New York, he was instructed by a flight attendant to remove his sweater that said Palestine on it. 

Does American Airlines have a bias towards Palestinians? Is there a policy that enables this kind of targeting and mistreatment? 

He was devastated and felt like the erasure of Palestinians in our country has no limits. I emailed @americanair and I'm waiting for a response.

Palestinians exist. We are human beings. And we will not be erased.
We will always have each other’s backs 🫶🏿🫶🏽

I wish my Yaba was alive to see his union stand up and courageously say: ceasefire now. 

@uaw.union supporting saving lives, no matter faith or ethnicity, would have brought him so much joy. Every single time I step into a UAW union hall, I feel at home, welcomed and part of much larger family that is about shared humanity and justice for all. The world can now see why. 

The UAW joins the American Postal Workers Union @apwunational in urging our country to facilitate a permanent ceasefire. Please take a moment and thank these unions for doing what is right. 

This is an unpopular war and the majority of Americans are demanding a ceasefire. It’s time for our country to join us.

I am not going to back down. We will win in 2024 because our campaign will be centered on people and a coalition of movements for justice for all. 

Thank you to everyone who attended our 2024 campaign launch today at UAW Local 600. I am so grateful for your faith in the work I am doing. 

Check out the link in my bio for volunteer opportunities, to donate and to purchase swag to show off your support. 

#rootedincommunity 
#neverbackdown

76% of Democrats. 

57% of Independents.

49% of Republicans.

It's time for @potus to save lives and call for a permanent ceasefire.
Watching the updates from Hani every single day has been heartbroken. These are war crimes. Don't look away.

CNN Poll in Michigan:
Trump 50% 
Biden 40%

The latest CNN poll should not be shocking. Just look at the actions of @potus and his Administration this past few weeks. Biden and his Administration are actively supporting war crimes being committed by Netanyahu and the Israeli government. 

We are literally handing over the weapons and bombs. 

President Biden rather lose his election than say no to Netanyahu's genocide.

We are deeply concerned for our client, Zahra Shaik, the mother of U.S. service member Ragi Sckak, who is currently stuck in Gaza. 

We urgently demand action from the White House.

The majority of Americans support a ceasefire. My colleagues need to understand that ignoring the masses will lead to ignoring them. 

How many more have to be killed? 

📷  @uaw.union
